                    enableLink="false"
                    enableWarnOnLeave="false"
                    getAltFromDAM="false"
                    getCaptionFromDAM="false"
                    image="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:7fa5e679-b948-44df-bfd7-36b25225bbdb/as/JimButler_low.jpg?dpr=1"
                    imageAlt="Jim and his family"
                    imageIsDecorative="false"
                    imageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    language="none"
                    linkAriaLabel="\0"
                    modalPanelId="\0"
                    model="custom-image"
                    modelFields="[image,imageAlt,imageMimeType,getAltFromDAM,imageIsDecorative,caption,getCaptionFromDAM,displayCaptionBelowImage,enableLink,target,clickBehavior,modalPanelId,enableWarnOnLeave,warnOnLeavePath,linkAriaLabel,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Image"
                    target="\0"
                    warnOnLeavePath="\0"/>
                <block_7
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Jim also finds support in other immediate and extended family members. He smiles over memories he hopes to always recall, of flying in the two-seater plane he and his son built and spending so much time with his sister.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_7>
                <block_8
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Resilience is key to research"
                    titleType="h2"/>
                <block_9
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Despite hurdles in Alzheimer’s research, scientists continue to examine potential paths toward disease modification. “Alzheimer’s is a complex disease riddled with unknowns,” says Dr. Olga Sánchez-Soliño, global neuroscience therapeutic area head, global medical affairs, AbbVie. “We need to keep on trying. We must be resilient and have hope. Such a big impact in Alzheimer’s is yet to come.”&lt;/p>&lt;p>Dr. Sánchez-Soliño also points to the critical role patients play in the search for potential treatments. “We need to work together with investigators and count on the incredible generosity of patients who are willing to participate in clinical trials,” Dr. Sánchez-Soliño says. “We are very grateful to these patients who contribute their time and energy to advance research.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_9>
                <block_10
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analyticsInteractionId="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    caption="Jim has acclimated to living with daily “hiccups” by smiling at and dismissing them. “I try not to get mad at them,” he says."
                    classes_commonCustomClass="\0"
                    clickBehavior="_self"
                    displayCaptionBelowImage="true"
                    enableLink="false"
                    enableWarnOnLeave="false"
                    getAltFromDAM="false"
                    getCaptionFromDAM="false"
                    image="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:18de9365-5a96-413a-a54f-9e129cbb9e59/as/jim-hiccups.png?dpr=1"
                    imageAlt="Jim Hiccups"
                    imageIsDecorative="false"
                    imageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    language="none"
                    linkAriaLabel="\0"
                    modalPanelId="\0"
                    model="custom-image"
                    modelFields="[image,imageAlt,imageMimeType,getAltFromDAM,imageIsDecorative,caption,getCaptionFromDAM,displayCaptionBelowImage,enableLink,target,clickBehavior,modalPanelId,enableWarnOnLeave,warnOnLeavePath,linkAriaLabel,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Image"
                    target="\0"
                    warnOnLeavePath="\0"/>
                <block_11
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>For Jim, participating in clinical trials is the least he can do to help researchers in the fight for treatments. “I really appreciate their efforts to try to find a cure,” Jim says. “If my simple job is to just go on in there and take some cognitive tests and get infusions every month, [I] want to contribute.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_11>
                <block_12
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Living now, every day"
                    titleType="h2"/>
                <block_13
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>In addition to leaning on family, Jim invests in each day as much as he can – at home with chores and in society with politics – as a way to cope with his diagnosis. Participating in Alzheimer’s advocacy through patient groups and clinical trials also gives Jim a sense of purpose and pride. “It’s like being part of the team,” Jim says. “If I can put a helpful face to someone who’s covering this ground, that’s making a big contribution.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_13>
                <block_14
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
